 To find the least value of $x$ that is a solution of $|{-x+3}|=7$, we need to find the values of $x$ that satisfy the equation $|{-x+3}|=7$. Since $|{-x+3}|$ is positive for any $x$ in the domain of the expression, we can write \begin{align*} |{-x+3}|&=7 \\ -x+3&=7 \; \text { or } \; -x+3=-7 \\ \Rightarrow\qquad x&=-4\; \text { or } \; x=10. \end{align*}
